{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos241.erdos_241 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos241.erdos_241.","id":"vf_c8c1769a3eb8314c","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #241: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $f(N)$ be the maximum size of $A\\subseteq \\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ such that the sums $a+b+c$ with $a,b,c\\in A$ are all distinct (aside from the trivial coincidences). Is it true that\\[ f(N)\\sim N^{1/3}?\\] Current best: Bose and Chowla \\cite{BoCh62} provided a construction proving one half of this, namely\\[(1+o(1))N^{1/3}\\leq f(N).\\]The best upper bound known to date is due to Green \\cite{Gr01},\\[f(N) \\leq ((7/2)^{1/3}+o(1))N^{1/3}\\](note that $(7/2)^{1/3}\\approx 1.519$). Prize: $100. OEIS: A387704. Tags: additive combinatorics, sidon sets.","id":"vf_ce91048ced024415","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/241.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_c8c1769a3eb8314c","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:241","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_c8c1769a3eb8314c","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_ce91048ced024415","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_ce91048ced024415","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:241","trust":"signed"}],"external_